<emphasis id="B910EA985A7F980BF839F8A7E66CF88C" bold="true" box="[1998,2153,1796,1825]" pageId="8" pageNumber="201">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C644D095A7F980BF788F8A7E616F8E4" authority="A. Smith, 1833" authorityName="Lacepede" authorityYear="1799" class="Mammalia" family="Chrysochloridae" genus="Chrysochloris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Afrosoricida" pageId="8" pageNumber="201" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" species="villosa">Chrysochloris villosa A. Smith, 1833</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation id="3B0C3CD75A7F980BF7D4F893E7BDF8E4" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3804714313" box="[2083,2488,1840,1865]" pageId="8" pageNumber="201">KwaZulu-Natal, South Africa.</materialsCitation>
Widely used specific name villosus and sub- specific names rufopallidus and rufus have been changed for gender agreement. Six subspecies recognized, but subspecific taxonomy requires reassessment.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
